  <data name="LegalDisclaimerMarkdown" xml:space="preserve">
    <value># Disclaimer

*Cofrox — User Disclaimer*

By installing or using Cofrox, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to this disclaimer in full.

## 1. Your Responsibility for Content

You are solely responsible for the files you choose to convert using this application. You must ensure that you have the legal right to convert, copy, reproduce, or modify any file before doing so. Converting copyrighted content without authorization from the rights holder may violate copyright law in your jurisdiction. The developers of Cofrox are not responsible for how you use this application or for any legal consequences arising from your use.

## 2. No Warranty

Cofrox is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, accuracy of conversion output, or non-infringement. The developers do not guarantee that the application will be error-free or that conversion results will be accurate or complete.

## 3. Limitation of Liability

To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, in no event shall the developers of Cofrox be liable for any loss of data, file corruption, loss of profits, or any direct, indirect, incidental, special, exemplary, or consequential damages arising out of or in connection with the use or inability to use this application.

## 4. Third-Party Conversion Engines

Cofrox uses open source tools including FFmpeg, ImageMagick, Ghostscript, Pandoc, LibreOffice, and others to perform conversions. These tools are governed by their own licenses and are not developed or maintained by the Cofrox team. The developers of Cofrox are not responsible for the behavior, accuracy, or output quality of these third-party engines.

## 5. Codec and Format Licensing

Certain media formats (including but not limited to H.264, H.265/HEVC, AAC, and MP3) may be subject to patent royalties or licensing requirements in certain jurisdictions. You are responsible for ensuring that your use of this application complies with all applicable laws and licensing obligations in your country or region.

## 6. No Legal Advice

Nothing in this application or its documentation constitutes legal advice. If you have questions about the legality of converting a specific file or using a specific format, consult a qualified legal professional.</value>
